snippet.textDisplay:
For Yhorm, I have this little fun interaction between him and Siegward.  I can't take credit for it, but it's stuck with me every time I watch a Dark Souls 3 video.  All credit for it goes to it's original creator, Album Interpretations.

"I have... a request..." The giant sighed
"Ah, and what may that be my friend?" The knight replied, worry in his voice.
"Should I ever forsake my duty, abandon the world..." The giant reached behind him, and retrieved a sword, small and pitiful in his massive hands. "Please. Take this weapon. The only thing to strike me down... Relieve me of my duty, should it come to that."
The knight took the sword in his hands, a greatsword fit for a man. He looked solemnly up to the giant
"Of course, old friend. If that is your request, it shall be so."
The Giant sighed, relieved at his answer. "I thank you, my friend. I fear my people will forsake me, and I do not wish for this world to end, long as you live on in it." Outside the hall, people yelled, a protestant cheer. "And how do we know, he can keep us safe?!" One yelled.
"Please. Leave me to my people. I thank you for your promise, and do not wish you harm." The giant warned.
The knight nodded, understanding. "I shall make a quest of my own then, see the world."
The giant smiled.
The knight put his hand reassuringly on his friend. "Fear not! A knight of Catarina shall not fail his duty!"
The Giant let out a chuckle, a low, warm sound like a great old drum. "Of course not."
